Reasoning: The paper deals with learning guarantees for Multi-Task Learning (MTL) and provides a new bound on the Local Rademacher Complexity (LRC) for norm regularized as well as strongly convex hypothesis classes. This makes it highly likely that the paper belongs to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also deals with image classification tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions natural language processing tasks, which could place it in the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of concentration inequalities and statistical analysis suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with statistical learning theory, which could place it in the Statistics (cs.ST) sub-category.
